S3.title: 【ライブ】オンライン自習室 #作業用 #勉強 #自習室 study with me 2025-04-28 14:17
S3.description:
チャットで入れるオンライン作業部屋。

世界初のYoutubeライブ映像＆チャットを利用した完全自動型のオンライン入退室システム（人数無制限）（24時間）配信です。

自習室というタイトルではありますが、ここでは勉強以外のさまざまな作業（散歩，ヨガ，仮眠，瞑想，ゲーム，掃除など）もできます。

※スパム防止のため、チャンネル登録者のみモードになることがあります🙏そのときはチャンネル登録するとすぐに利用できます。

🔰【使い方】🔰
どなたでも今すぐ入室できます！
最初は次の2つのコマンドだけおぼえれば十分です。

・ルームに入って作業を始める
チャットに「!in」と書く。
作業内容もつけたい場合は「!in  作業内容」と書く。

・ルームを出る
チャットに「!out」と書く。

Botから返事があるまで待ってください。

コマンド一覧：https://kani3camp.github.io/youtube-study-space/docs/essential


🍉【作業名を書くには】🍉
・入室するときに「!in   国語」のように書く。
・すでに入室している場合は、「!change   国語」のように書く。

【作業名の規制に関して】
このオンライン作業部屋では、あえて自由度の高い作業名の表現を許容しています。そのため、勉強とは関係ない作業名が目に入ることがあります。ご了承ください。


🍫【主なコマンド】🍫
・!seat
今座っている座席番号と、入室からの経過時間、自動退室までの残り時間をBotが教えてくれます。

・!席番号
席を指定して入室できます。空いている座席を画面から探してください。
（例：「!32」で32番の席に入室）

・!more
作業時間を延長する。（例：「!more  100」で100分延長）

・!break
入室中に少し休憩する。基本15分、最大30分。

・!change
作業名や入室時間の変更をする。入室時間とは、入室してから自動退室までの時間。
（例：「!change  work  数学  min  70」で作業名を数学にして、入室時間を70分に変更する。例えば入室から30分経っていたら、自動退室まで40分が設定される。）

・!info
累計作業時間と、本日の累計作業時間をBotが教えてくれます。

・!report
⚠️緊急時以外使用しないでください！⚠️ 
管理人とモデレーターに連絡がいきます。スペースをあけて報告内容を書いてください。
例：「!report  荒らしがいます」「!report  100番席の作業名が不快です」
※管理人やモデレーターがすぐに来れないこともあります。
※質問や問い合わせは、!reportではなく概要欄にある問い合わせフォームから。

・コマンド一覧：https://kani3camp.github.io/youtube-study-space/docs/essential


🌈【座席の色について】🌈
累積作業時間に応じて席の色が変化します。
座席の色分け：https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/3fc22ea1b4214b3f976b03331c51d113

🎓【ランク機能】🎓
ベータ版のランクポイント(RP)システムを導入してます
ルール：https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/RP-977cf4a86075448ebe94f0fcebc7a5d3


🍊【お知らせ】🍊2025/03/20 更新
・2025/03/20 コマンド説明書を更新しました！ところどころ変わっています💡
https://kani3camp.github.io/youtube-study-space/

・2025/03/18 コマンドの書き方が少し楽になりました！コマンド説明書はこれから更新しますので、しばらくお待ちください。

・2025/03/12 【Q&A】更新しました。

・2024/12/31 アプデ
フード・ドリンクメニュー注文機能を追加しました。
画面右に表示されるメニューを注文することができます。
1日5回まで注文することができます（0時リセット）（メンバーさんは無制限）
コマンドの詳細：https://kani3camp.github.io/youtube-study-space/docs/basic#order

・2024/6/22 アプデ
画面デザインと、一部座席のデザインを更新しました。

・オンライン作業部屋の資料：https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/5021213988a34747a7513f1067deb76d

・視聴者交流用Discordサーバー：https://discord.gg/h9SenAvawT


🍹【チャット利用ルール】🍹
・チャットでの雑談は全然OKです
・作業に集中したい人はチャットを閉じましょう。

以下のような書き込みや行為は禁止されています。
・個人を特定できる内容
・特定の人に席を譲る行為
・複数アカウントを同時に使用して2個以上の座席を占有する行為
・他人を不快にする可能性のある内容・行為
・他の人の集中を妨げる内容・行為
・チャット上でメンションができない（またはしづらい）チャンネル名
・その他、モデレーターが不適切と判断する内容
禁止されたことを話すと、ブロックされます。
※作業名やチャンネル名も、不適切な表現はNGです。
詳細 https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/b25373358d9c4ff2bb5e080e02b1c4ef


❓【Q&A】❓
詳細は https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/FAQ-494da77e1cd5489298500c66866f47bd

Q. 座席に座ると何が起こるのでしょう？
A. 入室するとライブ映像内に皆さんの名前や作業内容が表示されます。

Q. この自習室を使う意味って何ですか？
A. 現実の自習室や図書館に行かなくても、他の人と同じ時間・空間で勉強しているように感じることができます。また、他の人の作業内容を見て、「みんなこういうこと勉強してるんだな」「この人私と同じことやってるな」などと思えて、モチベーションがあがる人もいます。

Q. 入室時間の延長はどこまで出来ますか？
A. やろうと思えば無限にできます。例えば「!more  m=100」を100分ごとに書き続ければいいです。ただし、１つの座席に座れる時間の上限があるため、途中で強制で席移動することがあります。

Q. 自動退室って？
A. !outをし忘れることがあるので、自動退室の機能があります。自動退室までの時間は基本120分・最大360分です。入室時に指定したり、延長したりできます。

Q. 作業の累計時間はリセットできますか？
A. 累計作業時間をリセットする機能は今はありませんが、今後、週ごと・月ごとの累計作業時間をカウントする機能を追加しようと考えています。

Q. 席を書いても後にチャットした人に席が取られます
A. 遅延によってあなたにだけそう見えています😓コマンドは順番通りに処理されます。https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/d85d84bad3b24e6f8e88601f9e74df0a をご覧ください。

Q. 画面右下のタイマーの時間割ありますか？
A. https://youtube-study-space.notion.site/385f89e0e7d14be7906555e1971f9ed0

Q. これいつまで配信してますか？始まりと終わりは何時ですか？
A. 24時間365日やっています。ただ、たまにメンテナンスをしたり、配信トラブル・システムトラブルが起こって一時的に視聴できなくなることもあります。

Q. Youtubeの画面を閉じても大丈夫ですか？
A. 大丈夫です。配信を見るのをやめても退室させられることはありません。

Q. 作業せず入るだけの人が出てくると思うのですが、そこはどう考えていますか？
A. その通りで、真面目に使わない人は必ずいると思います。気にしないでください。ちなみに、累積作業時間に応じて席の色が変わるランク表示機能は、他人と比較するためではなく、自分の努力の積み重ねの指標として活用してほしいです。

Q. フードサービスは本物の食事ではないですか。本物でないなら機能の目的はなんですか
A. !orderによる注文は、あくまで仮想的なものです。このオンライン作業部屋自体が仮想的なもので、そのなかでできることを増やしています。現実ではないですが、作業のお供として活用される方もいると思います。

00:00:00 Preparation
00:0 Start
03:0 Finish


◆5줄 일기쓰기 How to :
1. 노트나 다이어리에 【손글씨(중요)】로 5줄 일기를 쓴다.

날씨는 어땠나요?
입은 옷은?
먹은 것들
한 일들
오늘의 감상

2. 다 쓴 뒤 출석 체크를 한다. 
출석 체크 설문지 활용 https://forms.gle/xKE4cpxT7SkQ8MxY8
지속적인 동기부여를 위해서, 필수는 아님

3. 방송을 틀어 놓고 공부를 계속하거나, 독서 등 개인적인 활동을 한다.


◆5줄 일기쓰기의 효과
아주 간단해 보이지만 뇌를 풀가동 시켜 두뇌를 자극하고 기억력이 트레이닝 되며, 자율신경의 균형을 맞춰 스트레스를 경감시키는 좋은 방법이라고 해요. 매일 매일 남기는 기록이 오래 쌓이면 역사책이 되는 건 덤! 5줄 일기를 5년 이상씩 지속하는 분들도 있더라고요.

"일기를 쓰면 두뇌가 광범위하게 작동을 합니다. 우선 기억을 담당하는 해마로부터 하루의 사건을 꺼내고, 그렇게 꺼낸 사건을 어떻게 5줄로 구성할지 전두엽이 작동을 하고, 구성된 문장이 일시적으로 전두엽의 워킹 메모리(작업 기억)에 저장이 되며, 운동 신경을 통해 손끝에 지령을 내려 일기로 기록하게 됩니다.
습관화가 되면 일상 생활 속에 '안테나가 서 있다'는 것을 느끼게 됩니다. 막연하게 생활을 하는 것이 아니라 일기에 쓸 '토픽'을 찾게 되는 것입니다. 슬픈 일, 괴로운 일, 분했던 일 같은 부정적인 경험과 감정들 조차 '취재적인 관점'에서 보면 마음이 편해집니다." (출처 : 뇌신경 내과 전문의, 하세가와 카야)

혼자하면 동기부여가 약해져 작심삼일이 될 수도 있지만 함께 하면 지속 가능성이 높아지는 것 같아요. 수프도 꾸준히 하고 있답니다. 5줄 일기로 건강한 습관 만들기 함께 해 보는 건 어떨까요? :)

S8.title: 12 hour☘️ Study with me LIVE ☕ calm cozy ambience🩺POMODORO🔥Real-time study #Medgirl 2025-04-28 14:17
S8.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

이전에는 장교(ROTC 출신)로 해병대에 6년간 몸담았고, 전역 후 그간 배워보고 싶었던 영상 편집, 코딩, IT(네트워크, 정보보안 등) 여러가지를 공부 했습니다. 그러던 중 좋은 기회를 만나 쿠팡 자회사인 CFS에 입사. 물류센터에서 근무를 했습니다. 군인시절부터 조직(회사)에 의지 하지 않아도 되는 내 능력으로 내 삶을 살고 싶다는 생각을 자주 했고, 경제적으로 독립한 전문가(장인)가 되고 싶었습니다.

22년 11월 2차 시험이 끝나고 공부가 잘 되지 않아, 2023년 새해를 맞아 스터디윗미를 해보자는 생각을 했고, 열심히 실행하고 있습니다. 항상 시작이 가장 어려운 것 같습니다. JUST DO IT!!!그래도 해보는게 중요하다고 생각합니다.

미라클 모닝, 미라클 러닝, 공부, 독서 등 스스로 동기부여하려고 노력하고 있고, 가지고 있는 좋은 에너지들을 많은 분들과 주고 받고 싶어요! 부지러너 여러분들과 같이 2024년 목표 달성 해요! 들어와서 봐주시는 분들 정말 감사합니다!

This 24/7 stream from Studyistic is designed to motivate students anywhere, anytime! 📖During the study sessions (always 50 minutes), study as hard as you can!🫡 
📢Then in the 10-minute break there is room for relaxation. S38.description:
Hi ^^ We’re Anne🐷 & Adrien🐭!
We’re a couple who met during our university years. We’ve always supported and motivated each other to study and work hard to reach our shared goal: getting into medical school. And this year, we finally made it! We are now in our first year of medical school.

Through our YouTube channel, we want to connect with new people, share our journey in higher education, motivate others to study—and even motivate ourselves. We know how hard it can be to sit down and get to work.
Sometimes you feel like it’s already too late to start. Or you avoid trying just so you can blame your failure on not working enough—telling yourself it’s not because you’re not smart, just that you didn’t try. Or maybe you’re scared it will be too hard, so you don’t even want to begin.

But we need to stop being afraid of failure. Everyone  ail at something at some point. What really matters is learning from your mistakes and trying again.
The real failure is choosing to stay down instead of getting back up.


https://calendar.google.com/calendar/embed?src=54d9e9cd0925ec70b25ddff0cbaf1c740db60def939a3bccadebed2f9656aede%40group.calendar.google.com&ctz=Europe%2FBrussels

🍴 1h30 lunch break 🧀

What do you like to do during your breaks:
 - both : usually we try to do house chores so we can have a real break afterwards and not distract too much so we can get back to work more easily and answers to messages in the chat

 - Adrien : play games
What snacks do you enjoy while studying:

 - Adrien : really depends but either breakcore/dnb or ambiant sound
Who's the pig and who's the rat:
 - Anne : pig because she can eat anything with a refined palate, love the sun, and having naps under the tree shades
 - Adrien : rat because he belong to the sewer and is mischevious
What would you wish to become as professionals:
 - Anne : gastroenterologist or ophtalmologist or cardiologist or generalist
 - Adrien : neurologist
What are your hobbies:
 - Anne : ceramic, cooking and eating, painting, scents, being organized, keeping thngs tiddy and clean and wasting money on sonny angels but my most favourite thing is to spend time with my loved ones and making them feel happy and special
 - Adrien : wasting money on CRTs and electronics
What is your worst trait:

 - Adrien : laziness

 - Adrien : Anne's smile and laughter, and how she goes all out

 - Anne : Au bout du rêve (la princesse et la grenouille)
 - Adrien : 戦え (He's not japanese lol)


🎯 Chat Motivation
Feel free to share your study goals in detail for each session. Having a clear goal helps you stay organized, save time, and feel more motivated. Reaching your goals is super rewarding, so aim for goals that require effort but are still achievable.

🧠 Tips to Stay Focused

1. Start small
If you struggle to focus for more than 5 minutes, start with just 5. That’s already better than zero! Usually, the hardest part is just starting. So tell yourself you’ll work for 5 minutes—you might end up doing more, and if not, that’s totally okay. Start with 5 minutes of work and 10 minutes of break. Then increase slowly each day until you find the rhythm that works for you.

2. Set realistic goals
Plan your day with goals that are actually achievable. That feeling of success will motivate you to keep going—and maybe even push you to do a bit more. But always remember to keep it realistic. Feeling like you’ve failed can be very discouraging.

3. Talk to people during your breaks
Taking time to chat helps release pressure and puts things into perspective—like fears about falling behind or not being fast enough.

4. Don’t touch your phone first thing in the morning

[Pomodoro 50/10] STUDY WITH ME live on YouTube Rules!
1. Study for 50 minutes, break for 10 minutes.

Boost Your Productivity with My "Study With Me" Pomodoro 50/10 Live Session on YouTube

Looking for the perfect way to stay motivated and productive while studying or working? Join my "Study With Me" live session, where we use the powerful Pomodoro Technique to break down tasks into focused intervals. This method combines 50 minutes of deep focus with 10-minute refreshing breaks, helping you stay on track and avoid burnout.

Why Join This Live Session?

Stay Accountable: Working alongside others in real-time keeps you motivated and minimizes procrastination.

Structured Focus Time: The 50/10 Pomodoro cycle promotes sustained concentration, making it ideal for studying, writing, reading, or any productive activity.

Relaxing Study Vibes: Enjoy a calm and distraction-free environment with background music or ambient sounds to help you concentrate.

Community Support: Connect with like-minded individuals in the live chat who are also striving to achieve their goals.

Perfect for Everyone: Whether you’re a student preparing for exams, a professional working on a project, or simply someone with a passion for learning, this session is for you!


What to Expect:

1. A timer-guided Pomodoro session with clear transitions between focus and break times.


2. Tips and encouragement to help you maintain your focus.


3. A warm and welcoming space where you can share your goals, progress, and challenges in the live chat.



How the Pomodoro Technique Works:
The Pomodoro method is simple yet highly effective. You work on a task for a set amount of time (50 minutes in this case) and then take a short break (10 minutes). This structured approach:

Reduces mental fatigue.

Improves time management skills.

Encourages consistent progress without feeling overwhelmed.


Why Choose the 50/10 Variation?
While the traditional Pomodoro technique uses 25/5 intervals, the 50/10 variation is better suited for deeper work and more complex tasks. It allows you to fully immerse yourself in your work while giving your brain ample time to rest during breaks.

How to Join:
Simply click on the live session link and start working alongside me! Don’t forget to:

What You’ll Achieve:
By the end of each session, you’ll experience:

A productive mindset that sets the tone for the rest of your day.

🎓 Welcome to Guideway – Study With Me | CA Final | WAR Technique 📚

Hi, I’m a CA Final student and the face behind Guideway– a channel built for students like us who are striving hard to achieve big goals. Studying for professional exams like CA can feel isolating and overwhelming, but here at Guideway, you’re not alone.

I follow the **WAR Technique – Write, Analyze, and Revise**, a focused and strategic study approach that has helped me stay consistent and productive:

✍️ Write – Making active study notes and summaries to retain better  
🔍 Analyze – Understanding patterns from past papers and mock tests  
🔁 Revise – Regular revision to reinforce memory and stay exam-ready

Through my Live Study With Me sessions, I aim to create a virtual study room where we can sit down together, block distractions, and get things done. Whether you’re studying for your CA exams, CS, CMA, UPSC, or any other competitive exam – Guideway is here to guide your way.

✅ Pomodoro & Deep Work Sessions  
✅ Real-time accountability

✅ Motivation, consistency & no judgment zone

Let’s build discipline, conquer our syllabus, and walk confidently toward our dreams – one session at a time.

50 min study
